subject: Add presence to pcie-slots
commitMessage:
Add presence to pcie-slots

Using xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item's Presence field, we
export a status of either Enabled or Absent to indicate
presence of a device in a Slot.

This field can be set as needed by another daemon, in an example
case we have a presence pin being read by dbus-sensors and
exported via the Inventory.Item.Presence field.

TESTED: Ran Redfish Validator:
```
*** /redfish/v1/JsonSchemas/PCIeSlots
	 Type (JsonSchemaFile.v1_0_2.JsonSchemaFile), GET SUCCESS (time: 0:00:00.043911)
	 PASS
```

Signed-off-by: Cody Smith <scody@google.com>
Change-Id: I902bc29b762df7fa76208cd3dfc6f6f65c235f8b
